    "is_free": false,
    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" style=\"text-align: center\"><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2003490/extras/b95fe77499e556d45dcbd35a845021aa.webp?t=1766562871\" width=614 height=40 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Unravel the fate of the ocean as you glide across an ever changing seascape in the hopes of reuniting Toroa with their family on land.  <br><br>Following the winds of the Atua (Māori God) of the weather, Tāwhirimātea, Toroa will befriend creatures of the sea, meet distant relatives  while flying through dream-like clouds and lush oceanic environments grounded in the Māori world. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" style=\"text-align: center\"><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2003490/extras/9820f671895f48b877e65fd7994625ca.webp?t=1766562871\" width=614 height=40 /></span></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Toroa have the largest wingspan in the world! Glide on wind currents and explore stylised landscapes, from calm seas to  verdant islands and into dream-like cloudscapes. </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Creatures of the sea need your help. Chat with and befriend a colourful cast from the South Pacific including dolphins, whales, penguins and more!  </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Trade kelp with creatures and gather birds into a flock who will follow you all the way to the end of your journey. </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >With the help of a knowledgeable seagull, identify a smorgasbord of tasty looking trash strewn about the ocean (NOT FOR CONSUMPTION)  </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Experience a heartfelt story grounded in te ao Māori (the Māori world) centered on our precious ocean, family, past, present and future. </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Listen to a lush soundtrack showcasing the beauty of taonga pūoro (Māori musical instruments) and experience the beauty of the Māori language  in character dialogue and story.</p></li></ul>",
